###Block: Reincarnated Druid
Mysterious Stranger		KEY:Mysterious Stranger ~ Reincarnated Druid		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:ArchetypeDruid.SpecialQuality.Extraordinary	DESC:You add %1 to the DC of Sense Motive, Diplomacy, and Knowledge checks to learn about you.|MysteriousStrangerBonus	SOURCEPAGE:p.39	DEFINE:MysteriousStrangerBonus|classlevel("Druid")/2
Resist Death's Touch		KEY:Resist Death's Touch ~ Reincarnated Druid		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:ArchetypeDruid.SpecialQuality.Extraordinary	DESC:You gain a +4 bonus on saving throws against death effects, energy drain, and necromancy effects, and on stabilization checks when dying.	SOURCEPAGE:p.39
Many Lives				KEY:Many Lives ~ Reincarnated Druid				CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:ArchetypeDruid.SpecialQuality.Extraordinary	DESC:If you are killed, you may automatically reincarnate (as the spell) 1 day later.  You appear in a safe location within 1 mile of your previous body. At will for the next 7 days, you can sense the presence of your remains as if using locate object as a spell-like ability. If you are killed during these 7 days, you remain dead and do not reincarnate. The many lives ability does not function you are slain by a death effect.  You cannot be raised from the dead orresurrected, though you can be reincarnated.	SOURCEPAGE:p.39
Cheat Death				KEY:Cheat Death ~ Reincarnated Druid			CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:ArchetypeDruid.SpecialQuality.Extraordinary	DESC:Once per day you may reroll a save against a death effect, energy drain, or necromancy effect before the result of the roll is revealed, or reroll a failed stabilization check while dying.  You must taket the result of the second roll, even if it is worse than the original roll.	SOURCEPAGE:p.39
Tongue of the Sun and Moon	KEY:Tongue of the Sun and Moon ~ Reincarnated Druid	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:ArchetypeDruid.SpecialQuality.Extraordinary	DESC:You can speak with any living creature.	SOURCEPAGE:p.39

###Block: Saurian Shaman archetype abilities
Nature Bond			KEY:Nature Bond ~ Saurian Shaman		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:ArchetypeDruid.SpecialQuality						DESC:If you choose an animal companion, you must select a dinosaur. If you choose a domain, you must choose from the Animal, Destruction, Fire, and War domains.	SOURCEPAGE:p.39	DEFINE:DruidAirNotAllowed|1	DEFINE:DruidWaterNotAllowed|1	DEFINE:DruidEarthNotAllowed|1	DEFINE:DruidPlantNotAllowed|1	DEFINE:DruidWeatherNotAllowed|1	DEFINE:DruidDestructionAllowed|1	DEFINE:DruidWarAllowed|1	DEFINE:DruidAnimalTerrainDomainNotAllowed|1
Wild Empathy		KEY:Wild Empathy ~ Saurian Shaman		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:ArchetypeDruid.SpecialQuality.Extraordinary			DESC:You can use your wild empathy ability with dinosaurs and reptiles as a full-round action with a +4 bonus.		SOURCEPAGE:p.40
Totem Transformation	KEY:Totem Transformation ~ Saurian Shaman	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:ArchetypeDruid.SpecialQuality.Supernatural				DESC:You may adopt an aspect of the saurian while retaining your normal form. You gain one of the following bonuses: movement (+10 enhancement bonus to land speed), scales (+2 natural armor bonus to AC), senses (low-light vision, scent), or natural weapons (bite [1d6], 2 claws [1d4] for a Medium druid, rake, +2 CMB to grapple). While using totem transformation, you may speak normally and can cast speak with animals (reptiles and dinosaurs only) at will. Using this ability is a standard action at 2nd level, a move action at 7th level, and a swift action at 12th level. You can use this ability for %1 minutes per day. These minutes do not need to be consecutive, but they must be used in 1-minute increments. This is a polymorph effect and cannot be used while you are using another polymorph effect, such as wild shape.|TotemTransformationDuration	DEFINE:TotemTransformationDuration|classlevel("Druid")	SOURCEPAGE:p.40
Totemic Summons		KEY:Totemic Summons ~ Saurian Shaman	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:ArchetypeDruid.SpecialQuality.Supernatural				DESC:You may cast summon nature's ally as a standard action when summoning reptiles and dinosaurs, and those summoned creatures gain %1 temporary hit points. You can apply the young template to any reptile or dinosaur to reduce the level of the summoning spell required by one. You can also increase the level of summoning required by one in order to apply either the advanced or the giant template, or increase it by two to apply both the advanced and giant templates.|TotemicSummonsTempHP	DEFINE:TotemicSummonsTempHP|classlevel("Druid")		SOURCEPAGE:p.40
# TODO: Need a method to separate out the -2 and +2 for the selected form
Wild Shape			KEY:Wild Shape ~ Saurian Shaman		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:ArchetypeDruid.SpecialQuality.Supernatural.DruidWildShape	DESC:Your wild shape ability functions at your druid level - 2. If you take on the form of a reptile or dinosaur, you instead use your druid level +2.	SOURCEPAGE:p.40
Saurian Shaman Bonus Feats	CATEGORY:Internal		BONUS:ABILITYPOOL|Saurian Shaman Bonus Feat|SaurianShamanBonusFeats	DEFINE:SaurianShamanBonusFeats|(classlevel("Druid")-5)/4

